        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 5:00PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 459 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 6 miles south of Fowler to
18 miles southwest of Olney Springs to 13 miles south of Avondale.
Movement was north at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fowler and Olney Springs.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
